The paper proposes a machine learning-based framework for vehicle trajectory prediction in vehicular networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves computer vision techniques for predicting the two-dimensional trajectory of vehicles, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the second likely category. The paper also deals with control and optimization problems related to vehicle maneuver prediction, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the impact of communication quality on the prediction accuracy, which could be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
